es. LLM-DEP: correctness target here is successful end-to-end delivery, not evaluation of model output quality. MULTI-STEP: not defined as multi-agentic reasoning chain. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Agentic because behavior text focuses on \"reaches ... inbox correctly\" (transport/system outcome), not whether model-generated narrative is semantically correct.","test_description":"Execute the script in a production-like environment against real staging endpoints and a real test mailbox; verify one run produces an email in the configured inbox with expected subject, recipient, and attached/embedded report sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.14,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: failure/recovery spans real filesystem persistence plus cross-run retry behavior tied to scheduler/runtime conditions. MOCK-HIDE: fake FS/scheduler often misses path/permission/atomic-write and run-to-run state issues. LLM-DEP: not about model output quality. MULTI-STEP: sequence is temporal retry logic, not multiple agentic model decisions. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Integration because behavior text explicitly requires \"saved to a local file\" and retry \"on the next scheduled run,\" which are real environment boundaries.","test_description":"Run once with email endpoint intentionally unreachable; assert report file is written at configured path. Trigger the next scheduled execution with email restored; assert persisted report is retried/sent and retry state is cleared to prevent duplicate future sends.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.16,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
